      { question: "Rising transmembrane pressure (TMP) during CRRT most likely indicates?", options: ["Fluid overload", "Filter clotting", "Catheter malposition", "Hemodynamic improvement"], correct: 1, rationale: "Rising TMP indicates increasing resistance across the filter membrane, most commonly from clotting. If TMP exceeds threshold, the filter needs replacement." }
