      { name: "Thiamine (Vitamin B1)", type: "Water-soluble vitamin", action: "Essential cofactor for carbohydrate metabolism, prevents Wernicke encephalopathy during refeeding", sideEffects: "Rare anaphylaxis with IV push", contra: "None", pearl: "Give thiamine 200-300 mg IV BEFORE initiating nutrition in malnourished patients to prevent Wernicke encephalopathy. Refeeding without thiamine can be fatal." }
